1. Standard Ansible call

1.1 Pipeline version 3.0

    ansible-playbook -i prod-inventory playbooks/install.yml --ask-pass

1.2 Pipeline version 4.0

    ansible-playbook -i prod-inventory playbooks/install-v4.0.yml --ask-pass

2. Using verbose mode

    ansible-playbook -vvv -i prod-inventory playbooks/install.yml --ask-pass

3. Using tags to run a specific part of the configuration without running the whole playbook

    ansible-playbook -i prod-inventory playbooks/install.yml --ask-pass --tags "init,miniconda"

4. You may also apply tags to roles

roles:
    - { role: pipeline-v3.0, tags: ['production'] }


5. How to add the Conda Ansible Module (https://github.com/UDST/ansible-conda)?

5.1 Change the Ansible configuration and set library variable

    nano /etc/ansible/ansible.cfg

    library        = /usr/share/ansible

5.2 Download Conda module and unzip it in the library directory

    # You might have to do all those tasks as super user
    cd /usr/share/ansible
    wget -O ansible-conda-master.zip https://github.com/UDST/ansible-conda/archive/master.zip

    unzip ansible-conda-master.zip

5.3 Check if Conda module is in the list of install Ansible modules

    ansible-doc -l